      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 38
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade FD3S Mazda RX-7, powered by the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This specimen remains in an unmodified state, featuring a perfectly preserved vacuum manifold and solenoid rack, ensuring the seamless transition of the Hitachi HT12 turbochargers across the power band. The longitudinal front-midship engine placement and 50/50 weight distribution are complemented by a factory-fresh double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Mechanical health is superlative, with compression figures remaining robust and consistent across all rotor faces. The exterior retains its original high-depth luster, while the interior is free of the typical dash delamination or bolster wear found in lesser examples. This is an investment-grade, analog masterpiece for the discerning enthusiast.",
